def: A small South American edentate (Chlamyphorus truncatus, and C.retusus) allied to the armadillo. It is covered with a leathery shellor coat of mail, like a cloak, attached along the spine.
Of or performance to roots, or the root of a plant.

An open square in a European town, especially an Italian town;hence (Arch.), an arcaded and roofed gallery; a portico. In theUnited States the word is popularly applied to a veranda.We walk by the obelisk, and meditate in piazzas. Jer. Taylor.
The poachard. [Prov. Eng.] Poker picture, a picture formed inimitation of bisterwashed drawings, by singeing the surface of woodwith a heated poker or other iron. Fairholt.
An officer in the Greek empire having functions correspondingto those of a justice of the peace. [Written also eirenarch.]
To step over or beyond; to transgress. Shak.
The act of thrusting or pushing out; a driving out; expulsion.
Worthy of being depended on; trustworthy. "Dependablefriendships." Pope.
